Calling [phoneNumber()](http://dius.github.io/java-faker/apidocs/index.html) gives the correct Russian format.

```lang-java
Locale locale = new Locale(&quot;ru&quot;);
Faker faker = new Faker(locale);
System.out.println(faker.phoneNumber().phoneNumber());
// +7(979)761-86-72
```

The *cell_phone* format has not been added in the [Russia&#39;s locale file](https://github.com/DiUS/java-faker/blob/master/src/main/resources/ru.yml#L54), only *phone_number*.

So, we can use the above method to generate Russia phone numbers.

Note: Looks like [Moscow has different format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telephone_numbers_in_Russia#Calls_within_a_city_or_region) for Phone Number. I guess, there is no city-wise formatting in Faker.

