The initial error with your program is the use of the _[Scanner#hasNext](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Scanner.html#hasNext())_ method.

While your concept is correct, this is not the method you&#39;ll want to use when reading _standard-in_ input.

Essentially, the _Scanner_ will wait for more input, indefinitely.  
Thus, it is not a way to determine if the user has completed entering values.

Change this to the following.

```java
Car car;
String make, model;
do {
    car = new Car();
    car.setMake(make = scan.nextLine());
    if (make.isEmpty()) break;
    car.setModel(model = scan.nextLine());
    cars.add(car);
} while (!model.isEmpty());
```

Additionally, you need to change the subsequent _for-loop_ variable name, _car_, since we are now using that name.

Output

```none
Honda
Fit
Toyota
Corolla
Mazda
Axela

Honda Fit
There are 3 cars 
Toyota Corolla
There are 3 cars 
Mazda Axela
There are 3 cars 
```

Here are a few improvements you can make to your code.

