```Xml
&lt;servlet&gt;
  &lt;servlet-name&gt;dispatcher&lt;/servlet-name&gt;
  &lt;servlet-class&gt;org.springframework.web.servlet.DispatcherServlet&lt;/servlet-class&gt;
  &lt;multipart-config /&gt; &lt;!-- Add for supporting multipart request --&gt;
&lt;/servlet&gt;
&lt;servlet-mapping&gt;
  &lt;servlet-name&gt;dispatcher&lt;/servlet-name&gt;
  &lt;url-pattern&gt;/&lt;/url-pattern&gt;
&lt;/servlet-mapping&gt;
```

Docs of spring `MultipartResolver` recommend to set multipartConfig of servlet in method `customizeRegistration`, but it&#39;s called only for default DispatcherServlet in `AbstractAnnotationConfigDispatcherServletInitializer.onStartup` 

